1
00:00:08,009 --> 00:00:10,444
(Koi) Huh? What is this?

2
00:00:10,511 --> 00:00:13,013
(Takuya) Here.

3
00:00:15,516 --> 00:00:17,952
(Yosuke) Huh? This guy...

4
00:00:18,018 --> 00:00:21,021
(Kataru) Eh, was that the person Chiharu met at the hotel?

5
00:00:23,023 --> 00:00:26,961
(Yosuke) Chiharu-chan is the one who said she was in sales, right?

6
00:00:27,027 --> 00:00:29,463
(Ko) “Currently working part-time at a bookstore→

7
00:00:29,530 --> 00:00:33,467
It says, "Mr. Sasaki continues to write novels every day."

8
00:00:33,534 --> 00:00:35,469
(Takuya) I also read the same part about 100 times.

9
00:00:35,536 --> 00:00:37,972
But no matter how many times I read it →

10
00:00:38,039 --> 00:00:40,975
It only says that I work part-time at a bookstore.

11
00:00:41,042 --> 00:00:46,046
It doesn't say that I work for some company.

12
00:00:49,550 --> 00:00:51,552
(Yosuke) Haha.

13
00:00:59,060 --> 00:01:01,495
(Yosuke) To be honest, I was in the 1%.

14
00:01:01,562 --> 00:01:03,431
(Takuya) 1%?

15
00:01:03,497 --> 00:01:05,933
(Yosuke) It's the probability that Chiharu-chan is having an affair.

16
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:07,935
That's what I thought at first.

17
00:01:08,002 --> 00:01:09,937
>>It was surprisingly low.

18
00:01:10,004 --> 00:01:12,440
(Yosuke) I just thought it would be interesting to have an affair→

19
00:01:12,506 --> 00:01:14,442
I didn't think I was actually doing it.

20
00:01:14,508 --> 00:01:18,946
Because he's the one Takuya chose.

21
00:01:19,013 --> 00:01:23,451
But I think I'm doing 99% now.

22
00:01:23,517 --> 00:01:27,455
And when you think about it actually happening, it's not even that interesting.

23
00:01:27,521 --> 00:01:30,024
Even I feel bad.

24
00:01:32,026 --> 00:01:35,963
Ah... the man who had many affairs →

25
00:01:36,030 --> 00:01:38,466
I wonder what you're talking about →

26
00:01:38,532 --> 00:01:41,969
I know this because I have had many affairs!

27
00:01:42,036 --> 00:01:44,538
Adultery is...

28
00:01:47,041 --> 00:01:50,044
No one will be happy except me.

29
00:01:56,050 --> 00:02:05,993
♪～

30
00:02:07,495 --> 00:02:09,430
(Male) Thank you for your hard work. (Chiharu) Thank you for your hard work.

31
00:02:09,497 --> 00:02:11,999
(Female) Thank you for your hard work. (Chiharu) Thank you for your hard work.

32
00:02:22,009 --> 00:02:24,445
(Sasaki) Thank you for just entrusting me with your order.

33
00:02:24,512 --> 00:02:26,947
(Customer) Thank you.

34
00:02:27,014 --> 00:02:30,451
☏(ringtone)

35
00:02:30,518 --> 00:02:33,954
Yes, ABC Shibuya store.

36
00:02:34,021 --> 00:02:35,956
It's me though.

37
00:02:36,023 --> 00:02:51,972
♪～

38
00:02:52,039 --> 00:02:53,974
(Takuya) Um...

39
00:02:54,041 --> 00:02:55,976
(Sudo) Yes.

40
00:02:56,043 --> 00:02:57,978
(Takuya) Is Mr. Sasaki here?

41
00:02:58,045 --> 00:03:01,048
>> Ah, I left early.

42
00:03:02,550 --> 00:03:04,418
(Yosuke) Were you able to escape? (Takuya) No, did he run away?→

43
00:03:04,485 --> 00:03:07,421
I don't know, but apparently he went home because he felt unwell.

44
00:03:07,488 --> 00:03:09,924
>>I mean, I definitely knew Taku-chan was coming.

45
00:03:09,990 --> 00:03:12,426
(Takuya) Yeah, but how?

46
00:03:12,493 --> 00:03:14,428
(Yosuke) Lend me your shoes.

47
00:03:14,495 --> 00:03:16,430
(Takuya) What? (Yosuke) It's okay, just lend it to me.

48
00:03:16,497 --> 00:03:18,933
(Koi) Why shoes?

49
00:03:18,999 --> 00:03:22,436
(Yosuke) My ex-wife once gave me shoes as a gift.

50
00:03:22,503 --> 00:03:25,439
They were pretty nice shoes like this →

51
00:03:25,506 --> 00:03:27,441
I loved it and wore it almost every day.

52
00:03:27,508 --> 00:03:29,944
(Takuya) Is that it? (Yosuke) But from that day→

53
00:03:30,010 --> 00:03:33,948
For some reason, you've started to guess my actions.

54
00:03:34,014 --> 00:03:35,516
(Takuya) Why?

55
00:03:37,017 --> 00:03:39,954
(Yosuke) It was a shoe with a GPS installed in it.

56
00:03:40,020 --> 00:03:41,956
>> Oh no. (Takuya) Scary.

57
00:03:42,022 --> 00:03:44,458
(Yosuke) So this is definitely it. >> Seriously? Seriously?

58
00:03:44,525 --> 00:03:46,527
(Yosuke) Let's go. >> Yeah.

59
00:03:49,029 --> 00:03:52,032
(Yosuke) Huh? This way or this way.

60
00:03:55,536 --> 00:03:57,471
(Yosuke) No.

61
00:03:57,538 --> 00:04:00,474
So, this one or this one?

62
00:04:00,541 --> 00:04:02,476
(Takuya) Oh, stop it! Stop it...

63
00:04:02,543 --> 00:04:04,411
Hey, really, really, please stop.

64
00:04:04,478 --> 00:04:06,914
I bought these for myself because I want nice shoes →

65
00:04:06,981 --> 00:04:08,916
I bought it myself with a bonus.

66
00:04:08,983 --> 00:04:10,918
It's not like I got it from Chiharu.

67
00:04:10,985 --> 00:04:13,420
(Yosuke) What is it? >> Please get me the shoes.

68
00:04:13,487 --> 00:04:15,923
(Takuya) Eh, stop making it seem like it's my fault.

69
00:04:15,990 --> 00:04:18,993
>> But then, how did you know?

70
00:04:28,002 --> 00:04:30,504
(Takuya) Delicious. (Chiharu) Hmm, good.

71
00:04:35,009 --> 00:04:37,444
(Takuya) Today. (Chiharu) Yeah.

72
00:04:37,511 --> 00:04:39,446
(Takuya) I went to the bookstore.

73
00:04:39,513 --> 00:04:41,448
(Chiharu) Hey.

74
00:04:41,515 --> 00:04:45,452
(Takuya) In terms of work, I also study civil law →

75
00:04:45,519 --> 00:04:47,955
I thought I'd study it.

76
00:04:48,022 --> 00:04:50,958
(Chiharu) Hey, that's great.

77
00:04:51,025 --> 00:04:53,961
Which bookstore did you go to?

78
00:04:54,028 --> 00:04:55,963
(Takuya) At Shibuya Station...｡

79
00:04:56,030 --> 00:04:59,466
(Chiharu) Oh, maybe ABC?

80
00:04:59,533 --> 00:05:01,468
(Takuya) Eh, how did you know?

81
00:05:01,535 --> 00:05:03,404
(Chiharu) It's a business location.

82
00:05:03,470 --> 00:05:07,408
Manager Sudo and I were having a meeting at the hotel the other day.

83
00:05:07,474 --> 00:05:10,411
Wasn't Sasaki-kun there?

84
00:05:10,477 --> 00:05:12,913
(Takuya) The store manager was there, but →

85
00:05:12,980 --> 00:05:16,417
I don't understand Sasaki.

86
00:05:16,483 --> 00:05:20,421
(Chiharu) Hmm, I see. Sasaki-kun is a part-time worker.→

87
00:05:20,487 --> 00:05:23,924
I'm good at my job and the store manager has a lot of trust in me.

88
00:05:23,991 --> 00:05:26,427
Just because you are busy, do it for us →

89
00:05:26,493 --> 00:05:29,997
I heard that Sasaki-kun is also responsible for our sales partners.

90
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:37,938
(Takuya) Seriously, sales... What do you think...｡

91
00:05:38,005 --> 00:05:40,507
Which...

92
00:05:51,018 --> 00:05:54,455
(Takuya) I'm going to the gym again today because I want to feel refreshed.

93
00:05:54,521 --> 00:05:56,023
(Chiharu) I understand.

94
00:05:57,524 --> 00:05:59,960
yeah? (Takuya) Oh no.

95
00:06:00,027 --> 00:06:01,962
Well then, I'll go.

96
00:06:02,029 --> 00:06:03,964
(Chiharu) Welcome.

97
00:06:05,966 --> 00:06:08,969
>> Well then, thank you for your hard work. (Takuya)...

98
00:06:21,982 --> 00:06:24,918
(Yosuke) Good work. (Takuya) Nice to meet you.

99
00:06:24,985 --> 00:06:28,422
(Yosuke) Come to think of it, I didn't ask, but what should we do?

100
00:06:28,489 --> 00:06:33,427
If the affair is confirmed, will we break up? Will you forgive me?

101
00:06:33,494 --> 00:06:37,498
(Takuya) Chiharu told me this before.

102
00:06:38,999 --> 00:06:41,001
"What would you do if I had an affair?"

103
00:06:42,503 --> 00:06:44,938
But me →

104
00:06:45,005 --> 00:06:49,443
I thought Chiharu would never do something like that →

105
00:06:49,510 --> 00:06:54,448
I said something nice, so I guess I'll forgive you.

106
00:06:54,515 --> 00:06:59,453
But I don't know if this actually happens.

107
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:02,890
I don't even know what to do.

108
00:07:02,956 --> 00:07:06,894
(Yosuke) Well, indecisiveness is your true charm.

109
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:08,896
(Takuya) What? that.

110
00:07:08,962 --> 00:07:13,400
(Yosuke) It means that no matter what answer you give, I will be on your side.

111
00:07:13,467 --> 00:07:15,969
(Takuya) Yosuke.

112
00:07:17,471 --> 00:07:19,907
(Yosuke) Just go ahead.

113
00:07:19,973 --> 00:07:21,909
(Takuya) Yeah.

114
00:07:21,975 --> 00:07:41,428
♪～

115
00:07:41,495 --> 00:07:44,431
(Sasaki's voice) I'll be waiting forever tomorrow.

116
00:07:44,498 --> 00:09:00,941
♪～

117
00:09:01,008 --> 00:09:02,876
(elevator arrival sound)

118
00:09:02,943 --> 00:09:12,886
♪～

119
00:09:12,953 --> 00:09:15,956
(Takuya) Ah... I'm sorry! I'm getting off...

120
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:30,904
♪～

121
00:09:30,971 --> 00:09:34,975
(Takuya) That's right, that's right, damn it!

122
00:09:36,977 --> 00:09:38,412
☏(Ring tone)

123
00:09:38,478 --> 00:09:40,414
(Takuya) Ah, sorry, I forgot that key→

124
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:42,416
I left the room, but could you please open it for me?

125
00:09:42,482 --> 00:09:44,418
☏(Staff) May I have your room number?

126
00:09:44,484 --> 00:09:46,420
(Takuya) Ah, I don't know which room that is.

127
00:09:46,486 --> 00:09:48,422
☏(Staff) We are very sorry.

128
00:09:48,488 --> 00:09:50,924
☏ We are unable to provide you with your room number.

129
00:09:50,991 --> 00:09:53,427
(Takuya) I made a reservation with either Yoshioka or Sasaki.

130
00:09:53,493 --> 00:09:56,430
☏(Staff) I'm sorry, but I can't tell you this...

131
00:09:56,496 --> 00:09:58,999
(Takuya) Yes, that's right!

132
00:10:00,500 --> 00:10:17,017
♪～

133
00:10:30,030 --> 00:10:32,466
>> It's scary that your whereabouts are being monitored.

134
00:10:32,532 --> 00:10:34,401
(Chiharu) That's right.

135
00:10:34,468 --> 00:10:37,404
>> Well, thanks to that, I can meet you with peace of mind →

136
00:10:37,471 --> 00:10:39,406
I can't say anything.

137
00:10:39,473 --> 00:10:43,477
(Chiharu) But he might be monitoring Sasaki-kun too.

138
00:10:50,484 --> 00:10:53,920
>> That's what I think. (Chiharu) Yeah.

139
00:10:53,987 --> 00:10:56,423
>> I'm Chiharu-san's husband →

140
00:10:56,490 --> 00:10:59,426
Even if my current husband were in my position →

141
00:10:59,493 --> 00:11:02,496
Chiharu-san has no interest in my whereabouts, right?

142
00:11:04,998 --> 00:11:07,934
(Chiharu) Why do you think so?

143
00:11:08,001 --> 00:11:12,439
>> Intuition of a future popular novelist →

144
00:11:12,506 --> 00:11:14,508
Just jealousy.

145
00:11:16,009 --> 00:11:27,454
♪～

146
00:11:27,521 --> 00:11:30,023
(Koi) Taku-chan, are you okay?

147
00:11:32,526 --> 00:11:34,961
Taku-chan, are you okay?

148
00:11:37,464 --> 00:11:40,400
(Yosuke) Huh? >> Taku-chan.

149
00:11:40,467 --> 00:11:42,402
(Yosuke) Huh? >> I wonder if it's okay.

150
00:11:42,469 --> 00:11:45,405
(Yosuke) Ah, it's going to be like that.

151
00:11:45,472 --> 00:11:47,407
>> I guess so.

152
00:11:47,474 --> 00:11:50,911
(Yosuke) I had no idea they were monitoring my whereabouts with this.

153
00:11:50,977 --> 00:11:54,981
>> Is the ability to search for lost items convenient or scary?

154
00:12:00,487 --> 00:12:02,489
(whistle)

155
00:12:21,508 --> 00:12:23,510
(room chime)

156
00:12:31,017 --> 00:12:33,019
(Takuya) I'm sorry, I'm really sorry.

157
00:12:34,955 --> 00:12:36,456
(sound of door closing)

158
00:12:43,463 --> 00:12:45,398
(Takuya) It's no longer possible.

159
00:12:45,465 --> 00:12:56,409
♪～

160
00:12:56,476 --> 00:12:57,911
(fire alarm sound)

161
00:12:57,978 --> 00:12:59,913
(Chiharu) Huh? >> What? A fire?

162
00:12:59,980 --> 00:13:01,915
(Chiharu) Hey, clothes, clothes. (Sound of fire alarm)

163
00:13:01,982 --> 00:13:12,425
(fire alarm sound)

164
00:13:12,492 --> 00:13:13,994
(Chiharu) Ah!

165
00:13:20,500 --> 00:13:30,944
♪～

166
00:13:31,011 --> 00:13:33,880
>> Was it you who pressed the alarm? Just check around.

167
00:13:33,947 --> 00:13:35,448
(Female staff) Yes.

168
00:13:38,952 --> 00:13:41,388
(Male staff) Does it look okay? (Female staff) Yes, it looks okay.

169
00:13:41,454 --> 00:13:43,456
Let's go together for a while.

170
00:13:44,958 --> 00:13:47,894
(Takuya) Ah, ah…｡

171
00:13:47,961 --> 00:13:50,897
Ah~! (Female staff) Hey.

172
00:13:50,964 --> 00:13:52,899
(Takuya) Ah!

173
00:13:52,966 --> 00:13:54,901
(Male staff) Security guard Security guard!

174
00:13:54,968 --> 00:14:03,410
(screams)

175
00:14:03,476 --> 00:14:05,912
[I was transferred to the Family Registration Division]

176
00:14:05,979 --> 00:14:07,914
(Chiharu) [Family Registration Division? ]

177
00:14:07,981 --> 00:14:10,917
(Takuya) [What is necessary for a person from birth to death→

178
00:14:10,984 --> 00:14:13,420
A place that handles all kinds of certificates]

179
00:14:13,486 --> 00:14:16,423
(Chiharu) [Wow, that's amazing]

180
00:14:16,489 --> 00:14:21,428
(Takuya) [Even within the city hall, we interact directly with residents →

181
00:14:21,494 --> 00:14:23,430
That's why it's called the face of government.]

182
00:14:23,496 --> 00:14:25,932
[That's why it's often a little difficult.]

183
00:14:25,999 --> 00:14:31,438
But I submitted my own request for transfer]

184
00:14:31,504 --> 00:14:33,940
(Chiharu) [Takuya? Why? ]

185
00:14:35,942 --> 00:14:39,879
(Takuya) [I want to be with Chiharu forever from now on]

186
00:14:39,946 --> 00:14:42,382
(Chiharu) [Huh? ]

187
00:14:42,449 --> 00:14:47,387
(Takuya) [Chiharu gives me stimulation and things like that→

188
00:14:47,454 --> 00:14:50,390
I'm so normal that I can't give you anything.]

189
00:14:50,457 --> 00:14:54,394
[So change yourself even a little →

190
00:14:54,461 --> 00:14:57,964
I wanted to try my best.]

191
00:15:05,472 --> 00:15:08,975
(Takuya) [I want Chiharu to like me more]

192
00:15:10,977 --> 00:15:15,915
[I was able to transfer, so the first thing I did was this→

193
00:15:15,982 --> 00:15:18,985
I was thinking that I would like to accept it.]

194
00:15:21,988 --> 00:15:24,924
(Takuya) 《In times of despair like this→

195
00:15:24,991 --> 00:15:29,429
Why do I remember my happiest times?

196
00:15:29,496 --> 00:15:31,498
[Please marry me]

197
00:15:36,436 --> 00:15:38,371
(Takuya) 《Oh no》

198
00:15:38,438 --> 00:15:41,875
《This is not a happy memory》

199
00:15:41,941 --> 00:15:43,877
[Chiharu? ]

200
00:15:43,943 --> 00:15:48,882
《At that moment, Chiharu stopped for a moment》

201
00:15:48,948 --> 00:15:52,452
``I always thought that was a surprise.''

202
00:15:53,953 --> 00:15:56,956
《Surprise at the sudden proposal》

203
00:15:59,960 --> 00:16:01,961
(Chiharu) [Yes]

204
00:16:04,464 --> 00:16:09,402
(Takuya) 《But I'm sure that was just hesitation》

205
00:16:09,469 --> 00:16:14,407
《Hesitation about marrying me》

206
00:16:14,474 --> 00:16:16,910
[Let's be happy]

207
00:16:16,976 --> 00:16:18,979
(Chiharu) [Yeah]

208
00:16:31,491 --> 00:16:34,861
(Takuya) Will tomorrow morning be the same as usual?

209
00:16:34,928 --> 00:16:36,863
(Chiharu) Huh?

210
00:16:36,930 --> 00:16:39,366
(Takuya) Coffee and bread→

211
00:16:39,432 --> 00:16:44,871
Isn't it okay to have the same fruit and yogurt as usual?

212
00:16:44,938 --> 00:16:47,941
(Chiharu) Takuya? (Takuya) I prefer the same as usual.

213
00:16:49,943 --> 00:16:51,945
Chiharu is good too, right?

214
00:16:53,947 --> 00:16:55,949
(Chiharu) Takuya.

215
00:16:59,452 --> 00:17:02,389
(Takuya) Isn't it okay?

216
00:17:02,455 --> 00:17:04,958
Let's do the same as usual.

217
00:17:11,965 --> 00:17:13,967
(Chiharu) I'm sorry.

218
00:17:17,971 --> 00:17:19,973
(Takuya) Is it no good?

219
00:17:23,476 --> 00:17:26,479
(Takuya) Isn't it okay for Chiharu to stay the same as always?

220
00:17:30,483 --> 00:17:32,986
(Takuya) Hey, wasn't that bad!?

221
00:17:35,488 --> 00:17:37,424
Is it because I’m boring?

222
00:17:37,490 --> 00:17:39,993
Is it more interesting to be with him? Is it fun?

223
00:17:41,995 --> 00:17:47,434
I'm an ordinary person, but I'm warm and calm.

224
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:51,438
That's why my life with Chiharu is so happy. It's important.

225
00:17:51,504 --> 00:17:53,440
Because I got it myself →

226
00:17:53,506 --> 00:17:56,509
I thought it was something that Chiharu and I made together.

227
00:17:58,011 --> 00:18:01,448
But...

228
00:18:01,514 --> 00:18:04,517
Why would Chiharu take that away?

229
00:18:06,019 --> 00:18:07,954
(Chiharu) I'm sorry. (Takuya) Ah...｡

230
00:18:08,021 --> 00:18:11,024
I don't want you to apologize, I just want to know why.

231
00:18:17,530 --> 00:18:19,466
(Takuya) Is it because he has talent? Because I'm normal →

232
00:18:19,532 --> 00:18:21,968
Did you have an affair with him? (Chiharu) No.

233
00:18:22,035 --> 00:18:24,037
(Takuya) Then why?

234
00:18:27,540 --> 00:18:31,978
(Chiharu) In place of myself who couldn't become an editor →

235
00:18:32,045 --> 00:18:36,483
I certainly wanted to support his dream.

236
00:18:37,984 --> 00:18:41,421
If it wasn't my dream to become a novelist →

237
00:18:41,488 --> 00:18:44,924
I might not have chosen him.

238
00:18:44,991 --> 00:18:50,497
But I've never compared him to Takuya.

239
00:18:51,998 --> 00:18:53,933
(Takuya) Do you think I'll be happy if you say something like that?

240
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:56,503
(Chiharu) For me, Takuya is the best!

241
00:18:59,005 --> 00:19:04,511
You may not believe it, but it's Takuya.

242
00:19:06,012 --> 00:19:09,015
I also really...

243
00:19:13,520 --> 00:19:24,964
